OL,3,CTyne and Wear Metro control room's
OL,4,C1990s technology to be replaced
OL,6,FIt will allow for faster and more
OL,7,Feffective fault finding, with the aim
OL,8,Fof providing Metro customers with less
OL,9,Fdisruption to essential facilities
OL,10,Flike lifts and escalators.
OL,12,FThe SCADA system is used to manage
OL,13,FMetro's power supply, fire and
OL,14,Fintruder alarms, lighting, lifts,
OL,15,Fescalators and tunnel drainage pumps.
OL,17,FThe current system, which is run from
OL,18,Fa desk in the Metro Control Centre at
OL,19,FSouth Gosforth, was installed in the
OL,20,Fmid-1990s.
